When I create a new branch and try to push it, in the push screen I check the new branch and it automatically fills the "Remote branch" field with the proper name. However, when I confirm the push, I get this error:

 

{{The Remote branch '' (Local branch = 'feature/test') is invalid. Ref names must follow git ref-format rules: }}
{{https://www.kernel.org/pub/software/scm/git/docs/git-check-ref-format.html}}
{{Completed with errors, see above.}}

 

I noticed that just deleting one char from the Remote branch name and reinsert it fix the problem.

 

The version I'm using is 3.3.4.

Sourcetree was working really well until I upgraded to 3.3.6 for Windows yesterday and now there are major issues with the interface:
 # The labels on the tabs has changed to the base folder name (this had been previously fixed);
 # When you click on a branch, nothing happens; you have to change tab, then come back to see the focus move to the selected node;
 # When you select changes to commit, nothing happens;  you have to change tab, then come back to see the selected changes move to the top window.
